obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (68278)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called “The Oudh Taluqdárs' Relief Act. ”`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68278&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (68279)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68279&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act---`
  line
  line `"Chief Commissioner" means the Chief Commissioner of Oudh:`
  line
  line `"aluqdr" means a person whose name is entered in the first of the lists mentioned in the Oudh "Estates" Act, 1869, section eight:`
  line
  line `"heir" means the person for the time being entitled under the same Act as heir to a taluqdar.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (68308)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to vest management of taluqdar's property in an officer appointed by Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68308&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, within twelve months after the passing of this Act, any taluqdár,`
  line `or (when such taluqdár is an infant, or of unsound mind, or an idiot) his guardian, committee, or`
  line `other legal curator,`
  line
  line `or the person who would be heir to such taluqdár if he died intestate,`
  line
  line `or (when such person is an infant, or of unsound mind, or an idiot) his guardian, committee, or`
  line `other legal curator,`
  line
  line `applies in writing to the Chief Commissioner, stating that the taluqdár is subject to, or that his`
  line `immoveable property is charged with, debts of liabilities other than debts due, or liabilities incurred to`
  line `Government, and requesting that the provisions of this Act be applied to his case,`
  line
  line `the Chief Commissioner may, with the previous consent of the Governor General of India in`
  line `Council by order published in the local official Gazette, appoint an officer (hereinafter called the`
  line `Manager), and vest in him the management of the immoveable property of or to which the taluqdár is`
  line `then possessed or entitled in his own right, or which he is entitled to redeem or which may be`
  line `acquired by or devolve on the taluqdár or his heir during the continuance of such management.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (68282)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Effect of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68282&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On such publication, the following consequences shall ensue:---`
  line
  line `Bar of suits against taluqdar.--- first, all proceedings in respect to such debts of liabilities which`
  line `may then be pending in any Civil Court in British India, shall be barred; and all processes, executions`
  line `and attachments for or in respect of such debts and liabilities shall become null and void ;`
  line
  line `Taluqdar freed from arrest.--- secondly, so long as such management continues, the taluqdar and`
  line `his heir shall not be liable to arrest for or in respect of the debts and liabilities to which the taluqdar`
  line `was immediately before the said publication subject, or with which his immoveable property or any`
  line `part thereof was then charged, other than debts due, or liabilities incurred, to Government ;`
  line
  line `and his moveable property from attachment for prior debts.-- nor shall their moveable`
  line `property be liable to attachment or sale, under process of any Civil Court in British India, for or in`
  line `respect of such debts and liabilities other than as aforesaid; and`
  line
  line `Cessation, of his power to alienate. thirdly, so long as such management continues,`
  line
  line `(a) the taluqdar and his heir shall be incompetent to mortgage, charge, lease or alienate their`
  line `immoveable property or any part thereof, or to grant valid receipts for the rents and profits arising or`
  line `accruing therefrom,`
  line
  line `Immoveable property freed from attachment. and (b) such, property shall be exempt from`
  line `attachment or sale under such process as aforesaid except for or in respect of debts due, or liabilities`
  line `incurred, to Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (68284)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Manager to receive rents and profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68284&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Manager shall, during his management of the`
  line `said property, receive and recover all rents and profits due in respect thereof; and shall, upon`
  line `receiving such rents and profits, give receipts for the same.`
  line
  line `From the sums so received, he shall pay--`
  line
  line `and pay therefrom the Government demand.--- first, the Government revenue, and all debts or`
  line `liabilities for the time being due or incurred to Government in respect of the said property:`
  line
  line `an annual sum for maintenance of the taluqdar and his heir.--- secondly, such annual sum as`
  line `appears to the Chief Commissioner requisite for the maintenance of the taluqdar, his heir and their`
  line `families:`
  line
  line `costs of repairs and improvements.--- thirdly, the costs of such repairs and improvements of the`
  line `property as appear necessary to the Manager and are approved by the Chief Commissioner:`
  line
  line `costs of management, and the debts and liabilities,--- and the residue shall be applied in`
  line `discharge of the costs of the management, and in settlement of such debts and liabilities of the`
  line `taluqdar and his heir and their immoveable property, as may be established under the provisions`
  line `hereinafter contained.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (68286)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Notice to claimants against taluqdar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68286&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On the publication of the order vesting in him the`
  line `management of the said property, the Manager shall publish in the local official Gazette a notice in`
  line `English and Urdú, calling upon all persons having claims against the taluqdár or his immoveable`
  line `property to notify the same in writing to such Manager within three months from the date of the`
  line publication.
  line
  line `Copies of notice to be exhibited.—He shall also cause copies of such notice to be exhibited at`
  line `the Tahsildárs’ Kachahrís in the District or Districts in which the said property lies and at such other`
  line `places as the Manager thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (68287)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Claim to contain full particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68287&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every such claimant shall, along with his claim, present`
  line `full particulars thereof.`
  line
  line `Documents to be given up.----Every document on which the claimant founds his claim, or on`
  line `which he relies in support thereof, shall be delivered to the Manager along with the claim.`
  line
  line `Entries in books.---If the document be an entry in any book, the claimant shall produce the book`
  line `to the Manager, together with a copy of the entry on which he relies. The Manager shall mark the`
  line `book for the purpose of identification, and, after examining and comparing the copy with the original,`
  line `shall return the book to the claimant.`
  line
  line `Exclusion of documents not produced.--- If any document in the possession or under the control`
  line `of the claimant is not delivered or produced by him to the Manager along with the claim, the Manager`
  line `may refuse to receive such document in evidence on the claimant's behalf at the investigation of the`
  line case.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (68288)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Debt or liability not duty notified, to be barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68288&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every debt or liability (other than debts`
  line `due, or liabilities incurred, to Government) to which the taluqdár is subject, or with which his`
  line `immoveable property or any part thereof is charged, and which is not duty notified to the Manager`
  line `within the time and in hereinbefore mentioned, shall be barred:`
  line
  line `Provision for admission of claim within further period of nine months.—Provided that, when`
  line `proof is made to the Manager that the claimant was unable to comply with the provisions of sections`
  line `six and seven, the Manager may admit such claim within the further period of nine months from the`
  line `expiration of the said period of three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (68289)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Determination of debts and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68289&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Manager shall, in accordance with the rules to`
  line `be made under this Act, determine the amount of the debts and liabilities due to the several creditors`
  line `of the taluqdár and persons holding mortgages, charges or liens on the said property or any part`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (68290)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68290&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `An appeal against any refusal, admission or determination under sections seven,`
  line `eight or nine shall lie, if preferred within six weeks from the date of such determination, to the`
  line `Commissioner of Division to whom the Manager is subordinate, and the decision of such`
  line `Commissioner, or of the Manager if no such appeal has been so preferred, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (68291)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Scheme for settlement of debts and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68291&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `When the total amount of such debts and`
  line `liabilities has been finally determined, the Manager shall prepare and submit to the Chief`
  line `Commissioner a schedule of such debts and liabilities, and a scheme for the settlement thereof; and`
  line `such scheme, when approved by the Chief Commissioner, shall be carried into effect.`
  line
  line `Power to return scheme for revision.—Until such approval is given, the Chief Commissioner`
  line `may, as often as he thinks fit, send back such scheme to the Manager for revision, and direct him to`
  line `make such further enquiry as may be requisite for the proper preparation of the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (68292)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Restoration of taluqdar to his property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68292&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `When all such debts and liabilities have been`
  line discharged,.
  line
  line `or if, within six months after the publication of the order mentioned in section three, the Chief`
  line `Commissioner thinks that the provisions of this Act should not continue to apply to the case of the`
  line `taluqdár or his heir,.`
  line
  line `the taluqdár or his heir shall be restored to the possession and enjoyment of his immoveable`
  line `property, or of such part thereof as has not been sold by the Manager under the power contained in`
  line `section nineteen, but subject to the leases and mortgages (if any) granted and made by the Manager`
  line `under the powers hereinafter contained.`
  line
  line `Revival of barred proceedings and debts.—Where the taluqdár or his heir is so restored under`
  line `the circumstances mentioned in the second clause of this section, the proceedings, processes,`
  line `executions and attachments mentioned in section three (so far as they relate to debts and liabilities not`
  line `settled by the Manager), and the debts and liabilities barred by section eight, shall be revived, and any`
  line `mortgagee dispossessed under section seventeen shall be reinstated unless his claim under the`
  line `mortgage has been satisfied;`
  line
  line `and in calculating the periods of limitation applicable to such revived proceedings and to suits to`
  line `recover and enforce such revived debts and liabilities, the time intervening between such restoration`
  line `and the publication of the order mentioned in section three shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (68294)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to call for further particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68294&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Manager may, from time to time, call for further`
  line `and more detailed particulars of any claim preferred before, him under this Act, and may at his`
  line `discretion refuse to proceed with the investigation of the claim until such particulars are supplied.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (68295)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to summon witnesses and compel production of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68295&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of`
  line `this Act, the Manager may summon and enforce the attendance of witnesses and compel them to give`
  line `evidence, and compel the production of documents by the same means, and, as far as possible, in the`
  line `same manner, as is provided in the case of a Civil Court by the Code of Civil Procedure`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (68296)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to administer oaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68296&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Manager may administer an oath in such form as he`
  line `thinks fit to any person examined before him touching the matters to be enquired into under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (68297)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Investigation to be deemed a judicial proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68297&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Every investigation conducted by the`
  line `Manager with reference to any claim preferred before him under this Act, or to any matter connected with any such claim, shall be taken to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of the Indian Penal`
  line Code.
  line
  line `Statements of persons examined, to be evidence.—And every statement made by any person`
  line `examined by or before the Manager with reference to such investigation, whether upon oath or`
  line `otherwise, shall be taken to be evidence within the meaning of the same Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (68298)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Manager to have powers of a taluqdar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68298&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Manager shall have, for the purpose of`
  line `realizing and recovering the rents and profits of the said immoveable property, the same powers as the`
  line `taluqdár would have had for such purpose if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `Power to remove mortgagee in possession.—And if such property, or any part thereof, be in the`
  line `possession of any mortgagee, the Manager may apply to the Court of the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `within whose jurisdiction the property is situate, and such Court shall cause the same to be delivered`
  line `to the Manager as if a decree therefor had been made in his favour; but without prejudice to the`
  line `mortgagee preferring his claim under the provisions hereinbefore contained.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (68299)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68299&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the rules made under section twenty, the Manager shall have`
  line `power to demise all or any part of the said property, for any term of years not exceeding twenty years`
  line `absolute, to take effect in possession, in consdieration of any fine or fines, or without fine, and`
  line `reserving such rents and under such conditions as may be agreed upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (68300)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to raise money by mortgage or sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68300&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Manager, with the previous assent of the`
  line `Chief Commissioner, shall have power to raise any money which may be required for the settlement`
  line `of the debts and liabilities (other than as aforesaid) to which the taluqd�r is subject, or with which his`
  line `immoveable property or any part thereof is charged,`
  line
  line `by demising by way of mortgage the whole or any part of such property for a term not exceeding`
  line `twenty years from the said publication,`
  line
  line `or by selling, with the previous consent of the taluqdar and of the person (being of full age) who`
  line `would be his heir if he died intestate, by public auction or by private contract, and upon such terms as`
  line `the Manager thinks fit, such portion of the same property as may appear expedient.`
  line
  line `And no mortgagee advancing money upon any mortgage made under this section, shall be bound`
  line `to see that such money is wanted or that no more than is wanted is raised.`
  line
  line `Manager's receipts.—And the receipt of the Manager for any monies paid to him upon any`
  line `mortgage or sale made under this section, or for any rents or profits received by him under section`
  line `five, shall discharge the person paying the same therefrom and from being concerned to see to the`
  line `application thereof.`
  line `The power to mortgage conferred by this section shall not be exercisable until six months have`
  line `elapsed from the publication of the order mentioned in section three.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (68302)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68302&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, from time to time, make rules`
  line `consistent with this Act in all matters connected with its enforcement.`
  line `Such rules, when approved by the Governor General of India in Council, and published in the`
  line `local official Gazette, shall have the force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (68303)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to appoint new Managers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68303&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Chief Commissioner thinks fit, he may`
  line `appoint any officer to be a Manager in the stead of any Manager appointed under this Act; and`
  line `thereupon the management then vested under this Act in the former Manager shall become vested in`
  line `the new Manager.`
  line
  line `Every such new Manager shall have the same powers as if he had been originally appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (68304)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Managers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68304&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Every Manager appointed under this Act shall be deemed`
  line `a public servant within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (68305)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Bar of suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68305&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other, proceeding shall be maintained against any person in respect`
  line `of anything done by him bonâ fide pursuant to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (68306)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Petitions, &c., under Act exempt from Court fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68306&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No petition, application, memorandum`
  line `of appeal or other proceeding under this Act, shall be chargeable under the Court Fees Act, 1870.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (68307)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Saving of jurisdiction of Courts in Oudh in respect of certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612&sectionId=68307&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00103_187024_1663845783612
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act`
  line `precludes the Courts of the Province of Oudh, having jurisdiction in suits relating to the succession to`
  line `or rights of persons claiming maintenance from any immoveable property brought under the operation`
  line `of this Act, from entertaining and disposing of such suits; but to all such suits the Manager of such`
  line `property shall be made a party.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
